body:
@Riot Preseason Item Team, I saw all of the itemization changes like the regeneration stat changes, the new items, the redo of the jungle, etc. as I was reading around yesterday. I looked back at the list of removed items (jungle items and old elixirs and atma's) and I guess I missed that YOU REMOVED GUINSOO'S RAGEBLADE! this item is so cool and is amazing on anyone that can use its stats well, but you are just straight up removing it?!? that just doesn't make any sense. It has a really great niche as one of the strongest dueling items in the game, (idk why nobody uses it tbh) and you didn't even say, "we're taking it out" or "we're going to rework it" you just up and axed it when nobody was looking. What is even your reason for removing it? Please at least give a reason when you remove items, so that we aren't all left hanging without answers. 

Atma's I understand, it wasn't really cohesive as an item (early game item with a late game power spike and random stats?), the jungle items I get because you are redoing that, the elixirs for the same reason, but Guinsoo's Rageblade has no reason to get cut! It has amazing usefulness for any hybrid champ (Kayle, Jax, Akali, Poppy, and Xin Zhao in particular) and fits very well in it's role (even hybrid carry casters like Corki and Varus rock Rageblade).

Please don't kill any more of these hybrid champs or items! your game gets more and more homogenized and boring each time you do.

